The '''Embassy of Sri Lanka in Tokyo''' is the [[diplomatic mission]] of [[Sri Lanka]] to [[Japan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Embassy of the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka, Tokyo, Japan|url=http://www.mea.gov.lk/index.php/en/missions/96-japan/455-embassy-of-the-democratic-socialist-republic-of-sri-lanka-tokyo-japan-|publisher=[[Ministry of External Affairs (Sri Lanka)]]}}</ref> The current ambassador is Prof. Dhammika Ganganath Dissanayake the former Chairman of Independent Television Network of Sri Lanka <ref>http://www.srilankamirror.com/news/item/3583-dhammika-ganganath-to-be-appointed-japanese-ambassador</ref>

